&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Project Manager, Commercial Kitchen Technology&lt;/strong&gt; is primarily responsible for the technical and commercial preparation of large-scale commercial kitchen projects. The role focuses on co-developing functional and efficient kitchen designs, preparing detailed budgets and specifications, strategically requesting supplier quotes, and conducting thorough 1-on-1 comparisons of received proposals. The Project Manager ensures that clients receive a technically accurate, financially transparent, and fully substantiated proposal that aligns with project-specific requirements and wishes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the final stage of the preparation phase, the Project Manager ensures a smooth transition and handover process. This includes initiating a targeted project kick-off to warmly hand over the project to the executing parties, the contractor, and the client’s project manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Important:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;This position is primarily focused on the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;preparation and design phase&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;of projects. Daily on-site coordination and operational project management during the construction phase fall outside the scope of this role; however, you are responsible for a flawless handover to the execution team.&lt;/p&gt;
